bib.title: Atlas Of Neutron Resonances Resonance Parameters And Thermal Cross Sections Z=1-100

free_txt: Resonance parameters and cross sections were analyzed
The neutron radiative cross sections were measured in
a Maxwellian flux, other measurements are commented.
Scattering length (coherent amplitude) b is related to
elastic scattering cross section as follows:
Both values are based on independent measurements.
Resonance integrals (RI) are based on experimental
values, if no measurements then calculated from
resonance parameter values from 0.5 eV to highest
energy of the resolved resonance region.

Evaluation: The experimental results for nuclei
between H and Fm were critically surveyed,
renormalized and resonance parameters were deduced.
Cross sections and resonance integrals were given
where available, otherwise they were calculated using
